<br>
1. Characters should be able to worship any god they wish, or no god at all, unless they are a priest or priest-hybrid.  Worshipping a god not accepted in your own home city should carry some pretty hefty faction penalties.<br>
<br>
2. Character starting alignment should not be based on race, but instead on class and diety.  Either that, or changing alignment should be possible as one levels (every 5 or 10 levels.)  Have alignment factor into faction system, so evil alignment and evil alignment produces no affect (or good-good), but the more in opposition alignments are, the more of a negative faction adjustment their should be.<br>
<br>
3. If you are going to declare certain classes must be &quot;good&quot; or &quot;evil&quot; then incorporate some kind of in-game consequences for behaving contrary to your alignment.  The evil paladin should suffer some kind of consequence, just as the kindly necromancer, if they are intrinsically good or evil. <p>[56 Beastlord ] Zanros (Iksar) &lt;Dragejegerene&gt; Zone: Stromm<br>
[4 Wizard-alt] Kypin (Froglok) Zone: Stromm<br>
[3 Wizard] Relistan (Dark Elf) Zone: Firiona Vie<br>
Interested in a guild on Firiona Vie of role-play renegade dark elves that mean it?  Contact me.<br>
