<br>
/agree that the raid loophole on TLC should be fixed.  Because of it, uber players can still farm stuff from mobs that people of appropriate level should have a chance to kill.<br>
<br>
Alignment?  I like the idea.  As a peaceloving bard of Quellious, I wish we could all just get along in harmony, but hey.  A High Elf Paladin grouping with a Dark Elf Necromancer?  If it's going to be roleplay, some things should not be.<br>
<br>
/disagree about /roleplay.  I find it particularly silly when people are /lfg without their class and season showing.  Is it somehow more &quot;roleplay&quot; to have to spend 10 minutes in tells asking people their class and season so you can group?  bah.  Duelling?  Anyone who would accept a duel without knowing someone's class and season is an idiot.  /shrug<br>
<br>
Enforcing name and chat rules?  There are two major problems with this:  1) GM presence to enforce, and 2)  MAJOR subjectivity in enforcement.<br>
<br>
I do find spamming in /shout in PoK annoying.  I DO think that auctions in /shout should be a warnable offense.  I think there SHOULD be and /ooc channel, that we all know how to turn off, for /ooc crap.<br>
<br>
One nice thing about LDoN is that people are starting to USE the LFG tool.  Perhaps one day we will see less &quot;51 Bard LFG, pst&quot; in /shout.<br>
<br>
On a regular Blue server, believe it or not, /shout is actually used for /shouting...  When you see bright red accross your chat window, it is usually something important, like a cry for help or a train warning.  Not so on FV.<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts.  /shrug.<br>
