<br>
What's my point?  To a good RPer, the noise and shouts in PoK are reminiscent of the bustle and noise of any market square.  If I truly were to live in a world where 100% of its living population were adventurers, what kind of shouts would we be expected to hear?  I understand Julius Caesar passed legislation to close all the markets in Rome after a certain hour because of the noise.<br>
<br>
Or names, for that matter.  If I cross paths with a shadowknight named &quot;Iamawesome&quot;, who's to say that those letters are pronounced &quot;I am awesome&quot;?  Why not &quot;Eeam-Aw-Eesom&quot;?  A simple step into suspending one's disbelief.<br>
<br>
Even d00d-speak.  As an RPing character, I know my character doesn't have a name over his head, or that what a groupmember says, even though presented in text form, is really supposed to be a spoken word. So, why is it so unreasonable when I see a shout &quot;51 SK LFG&quot; or a group message &quot;INC scrawny gnoll&quot;, to know my character is actually hearing, &quot;Fifty-first Shadowknight looking for a group&quot; or &quot;Incoming a scrawny gnoll&quot;?<br>
<br>
In sum, I do think that everyone can do a lot to improve the RPing environment on FV.  No question: Non-RPers are indeed guilty of spoiling the fun in FV.  But RPers need to bare some of the responsibility too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1>Firiona Vie General Chat</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.246g<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

